node.text: 8-year-old Memphis Rose Hamman has found a best friend in her “awesome” service dog, Juliet. ❤️ Following a car accident that left her paralyzed, Memphis Rose connected with Juliet through Lori Griffith, the founder of the Chasin' A Dream Foundation, a local nonprofit that assists children with life-threatening diseases. The pair quickly bonded, and after 18 months of training Juliet was finally able to move into Memphis Rose’s home. "You could not ask for a better team than these two," says Juliet’s trainer. "People focus on the physical damage that Memphis Rose endures, but she also needs mental stability. Juliet is there for her and knows what to do. She gives Memphis Rose confidence." Tap the link in bio for their full story. l📷: Gayrene Meade

node.text: The James Bond franchise producers are aware of Idris Elba when it comes to the conversation of who will next play 007. 👀  Producers Barbara Broccoli and Michael G. Wilson discussed Daniel Craig's last outing as the famous spy in No Time to Die, and when asked if they've considered Elba to become the next Bond, Broccoli maintained they haven't fully begun the process yet — but said he is "a magnificent actor." 👏 "You know, it's been part of the conversation," said Broccoli. Link in bio for the full story. | 📷: Emma McIntyre/Getty
